cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to remove rain and haze from single images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of wavelet transform and dark channel prior also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimization using back-propagation, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
